{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 1}The word of Jehovah to Hosea the son of Beeri in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Aiiaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah and in the days of Jeroboam, son of Joash, king of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}Now Jehovah said to Hosea:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Go marry a wife with whorish instincts
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
who will bear you children by her whoredom,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For the land is continually going a-whoring from after Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
So he went and married Gomer, the daughter of Dibliam.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
And when she conceived and bore him a son, {\super\cf2\fs24 4}Jehovah said:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Call his name \uc1\u8220*Jezreel,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For yet a little while
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will avenge the blood shed at Jezreel upon the house of Jehu,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will cause the kingdom of Israel to cease. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 5}And it shall come to pass in that day,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
That I will break the bow of Israel in the valley of Jezreel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 6}And when she conceived again and bore a daughter, he said to him:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Call her name \uc1\u8220*Unpitied,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2080\li2800
For I will no longer
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Have pity on the house of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
That I should still spare them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 8}Then she weaned Unpitied; and when she conceived and bore a son, he said: 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 9}Call his name, \uc1\u8220*Not-my-people:\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For ye indeed are not my people,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I indeed am not your God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
Then Hosea said:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\i I will put away Gomer,}
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For she is not my wife,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will not be her husband;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And on her children I will have no pity,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Since they are children of whoredom,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For their mother hath become a harlot,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
She who conceived them hath behaved shamefully.
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 10}And the number of the Israelites shall be as the sand of the sea,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Which cannot be measured or numbered;
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And instead of its being said of them,  \uc1\u8220*Ye are not my people,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
They shall be called,  \uc1\u8220*The sons of the living God.\uc1\u8221* 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 11}And the Judahites and the Israelites shall be gathered together,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And they shall appoint for themselves one head, and they shall go up out of the land,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
For great shall he the day of Jezreel. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\cf1 2}Say ye to your brother, \uc1\u8220*My people\uc1\u8221*{\super\cf2\fs24 1}and to your sister, \uc1\u8220*Pitied\uc1\u8217*. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 2}Strive with your mother, strive,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
That she put her acts of whoredom from her sight,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And her adulteries from between her breasts,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Lest I strip her naked,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And set her as she was on the day of her birth,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And make her like the wilderness,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And let her become like a parched land,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And let her die of thirst.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 5}For she hath said,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
I will go after my paramour
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Who gave me my bread and my water,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
My wool, my flax, my oil, and my drink. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 6}Therefore I am going to hedge up her ways with thorns,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And build a wall about her,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
So that she cannot find her paths. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 7}And she will pursue her paramours,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
But will not overtake them,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And she will seek and not find them. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 8}But she herself did not know
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
That it was I who gave her
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The corn, the sweet wine, and the oil. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 9}Therefore I will take back my corn in its time,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And my sweet wine in its season,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will withdraw my wool and my flax,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Given to cover her nakedness; 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 10}And so I will uncover her shame,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And none shall deliver her out of my hand. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 12}And I will lay waste her vines and her fig-trees,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Of which she hath said, \uc1\u8220*These are my rewards
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Which my lovers have given me.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will make them a thicket,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And the wild beasts shall devour them. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 11}And I will also cause all her mirth to cease,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Her feasts, her new moon, and her sabbaths. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 13}And thus will I visit upon her the days of the Baalim,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
In which she made offerings to them,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And decked herself with ear-rings and jewels,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And went after her paramours,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And forgot me, is the oracle of Jehovah. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore I am going to allure her,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And bring her into the wilderness,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And speak endearingly to her. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 15}And I will give her from there her vineyards,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And the valley of Achori as a door of hope,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And there she shall respond as in the days of her youth,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
As in the days when she came up from the land of Egypt. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 16}And it shall be in that day, is the oracle of Jehovah,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
She shall call to her husband,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And shall call no more to the Baalim. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 17}And I will remove the name of the Baitlim from her mouth,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And they shall no more be mentioned by their names. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 18}And I will betroth her to me forever, 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 19}Yea, I will betroth hers to me in righteousness,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And in judgment, and in kindness, and in mercy, 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 20}Yea, I will betroth her to me in faithfulness and she shall know Jehovah!
\par}

{\pard 

\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
 {\super\cf2\fs24 21}And it shall come to pass in that day,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
That I will speak, \uc1\u8212* it is the oracle of Jehovah,\uc1\u8212*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
I will speak to the heavens,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And they will speak to the earth. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 22}And the earth will speak to the grain,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And the new wine and the oil:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And they shall speak to Jezreel,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will sow her in the land. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 23}And I will have pity upon the unpitied,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And I will say to Not-my-people, \uc1\u8220*Thou art my people,\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And they will say, \uc1\u8220*Thou art my God.\uc1\u8221* 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\cf1 3}But Jehovah said to me:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 1}Still go, love this woman,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Who loves a paramour and is an adulteress,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
As Jehovah loveth the Israelites,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Although they turn to other gods,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
And love raisin-cakes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 2}So I bought her to me for fifteen pieces of silver and eight bushels of barley and a measure of barley.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 3}And I said to her:
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Many days shalt thou abide for me,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Thou shall not play the harlot, and thou shalt not be any man\uc1\u8217*s wife,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Yet, I, on my part will be thine. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 4}For through many days
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
The Israelites shall abide
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Without king and without prince,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Without sacrifice and without pillar,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
Without ephod and without teraphim. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
{\super\cf2\fs24 5}Afterward the Israelites shall return, and seek Jehovah their God and David their king. and they shall come trembling to Jehovah and his goodness, at the end of days. 
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
{\super\cf2\fs24 18}And I will make for them a covenant in that day,
\par}

{\pard\fi-2440\li2800
With the wild beasts, and the birds of the heavens and the creeping things of the earth,
\par}

